==English==
===Etymology===
Old English ''[[cild|ċild]]''.

===Pronunciation===
*{{AHD|chīld}}, {{IPA|/ʧaɪld/}}, {{SAMPA|/tSaIld/}}
*{{audio|en-us-child.ogg|Audio (US)}}
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-aɪld|-aɪld]]

===Noun===

{{en-noun|pl='''[[children]]'''; '''[[childer]]''' (obsolete); '''[[childrens]]''' (nonstandard)}}

# a [[son]] or [[daughter]]
# a [[young]] [[person]], a [[minor]], especially one who has not yet entered into [[puberty]]
#some [[object]] which has a [[subservient]] or [[derivative]] role relative to another object
# a person who resides in the [[parental home]]
# a person with living parents

